# Marketing site — repo context and Git safety

At the start of work in this project, assume the following block applies (treat it as prepended to every user request for this repo):

```
This is the xsee-website repo.
Git remote must be: https://github.com/Shimi-Lieberman/xsee-website
Before committing, verify with: git remote -v
Do not push to any other repo.
```

## Before every `git push`

Run:

```bash
git remote -v
```

Confirm the output shows exactly:

```
origin  https://github.com/Shimi-Lieberman/xsee-website (fetch)
origin  https://github.com/Shimi-Lieberman/xsee-website (push)
```

If it shows `Xsee_Security`, another GitHub URL, or any repo other than `Shimi-Lieberman/xsee-website` — **STOP**. Do not push. Report the mismatch to the user.

Marketing site changes must never be pushed to the platform app repository.
